<p>Coaching transitions at blue-blood programs rarely go smoothly. When Mike Krzyzewski stepped away in 2022, Duke faced the same uncertainty that often derails historic programs, but Jon Scheyer has defied that trend.</p>
<p>Instead of a drop-off, Duke has remained one of college basketball’s most consistent winners. The numbers show why.</p>
